Make up giant Sephora's much-awaited first Australian store opening was overshadowed by a glaring typo on their Facebook page.

If they were hoping to attract attention to the store's opening in Sydney on Friday, they certainly did so, but perhaps not in the way they were intending. 

On the store's 'Countdown to Beauty' hashtag, they missed the essential letter 'o' in count, leaving a particularly bad swear word on the page instead.

The slip-up has caused plenty of laughter and no shortage of commentary on social media, with some even suggesting the slip-up was actually a case of 'any publicity is good publicity'.  

